		<h1>Perfect Flat Iron Steak</h1>
		<p>We are going to make the perfect Flat Iron Steak</p>
		<p><strong>Prep Time:</strong>5 minutes, <strong>Cook Time:</strong>10 minutes, <strong>Servings:</strong>6</p>
		<ol>
			<li>1 (2 pound) Flat iron steak</li>
			<li>2 1/2 tablespoons olive oil</li>
			<li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li>
		</ol>
		<p><strong>Step 1</strong><br>Place steak inside a large resealable bag. Stir olive oil, garlic, parsley, rosemary, chives, red wine, salt, pepper, and mustard powder together in a small bowl.<br><br><strong>Step 2</strong><br>Pour marinade over steak in the bag. Press out as much air as you can and seal the bag. Marinate in the refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.
